Column.name: CUT_OFF_DATE_OFFSET
Column.commentInRDBMS: Number of days cut-off date for entries is offset from end of period.

Column.name: DIRECT_DEPOSIT_DATE_OFFSET
Column.commentInRDBMS: Number of days regular direct deposit date is offset from end of period.

Column.name: FIRST_PERIOD_END_DATE
Column.commentInRDBMS: End date of the first processing period. Used to generate first and all successive pay period dates for this payroll.

Column.name: NEGATIVE_PAY_ALLOWED_FLAG
Column.commentInRDBMS: Indicates whether negative payments are allowed.

Column.name: NUMBER_OF_YEARS
Column.commentInRDBMS: Number of years of pay periods to generate.

Column.name: PAY_ADVICE_DATE_OFFSET
Column.commentInRDBMS: Number of days regular pay advice is offset from end of period.

Column.name: PAY_DATE_OFFSET
Column.commentInRDBMS: Number of days regular pay date is offset from end of period.

Column.name: WORKLOAD_SHIFTING_LEVEL
Column.commentInRDBMS: Indicates whether workload shifting is enabled, and at what levels. Not currently implemented.

Column.name: MIDPOINT_OFFSET
Column.commentInRDBMS: Number of days to offset midpoint date for semi-monthly processing period.

Column.name: ARREARS_FLAG
Column.commentInRDBMS: Indicates whether payroll is an arrears payroll.

Column.name: LAST_UPDATE_DATE
Column.commentInRDBMS: Standard Who column - date when a user last updated this row.

Column.name: LAST_UPDATED_BY
Column.commentInRDBMS: Standard who column - user who last updated this row (foreign key to FND_USER.USER_ID).

Column.name: LAST_UPDATE_LOGIN
Column.commentInRDBMS: Standard who column - operating system login of user who last updated this row (foreign key to FND_LOGINS.LOGIN_ID).

Column.name: CREATED_BY
Column.commentInRDBMS: Standard who column - user who created this row (foreign key to FND_USER.USER_ID).

Column.name: CREATION_DATE
Column.commentInRDBMS: Standard who column - date when this row was created.

Column.name: PAYROLL_TYPE
Column.commentInRDBMS: Identifies the type of Payroll defined.

Column.name: MULTI_ASSIGNMENTS_FLAG
Column.commentInRDBMS: Indicates whether payroll is to process multiple assignments accumulatively

Column.name: PERIOD_RESET_YEARS
Column.commentInRDBMS: Number of Years after which the payroll periods would be reset. Used for Lunar Month Period Types.

Column.name: OBJECT_VERSION_NUMBER
Column.commentInRDBMS: System-generated version of row. Increments by one with each update.

Column.name: PAYSLIP_VIEW_DATE_OFFSET
Column.commentInRDBMS: Number of days after payment date, on or after which, user can view his payslip
